  "chapter": {
    "number": 57,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Blessed Death of the Righteous"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The righteous perish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no one takes it to heart;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "devout men are swept away,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while no one considers",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that the righteous are guided",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the presence of evil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those who walk uprightly enter into peace;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they find rest, lying down in death.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God Condemns Idolatry"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“But come here, you sons of a sorceress,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you offspring of adulterers and prostitutes!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whom are you mocking?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "At whom do you snarl and stick out your tongue?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Are you not children of transgression,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "offspring of deceit,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who burn with lust among the oaks,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "under every luxuriant tree,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who slaughter your children in the valleys,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "under the clefts of the rocks?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your portion is among the smooth stones of the valley;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "indeed, they are your lot.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Even to them you have poured out a drink offering",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and offered a grain offering.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Should I relent because of these?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On a high and lofty hill you have made your bed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there you went up to offer sacrifices.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behind the door and doorpost",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have set up your memorial.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Forsaking Me, you uncovered your bed;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you climbed up and opened it wide.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And you have made a pact with those whose bed you have loved;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have gazed upon their nakedness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You went to Molech",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2716
          },
          {
            "text": "with oil",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and multiplied your perfumes.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have sent your envoys",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2717
          },
          {
            "text": "a great distance;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have descended even to Sheol itself.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You are wearied by your many journeys,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but you did not say, “There is no hope!”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You found renewal of your strength;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "therefore you did not grow weak.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whom have you dreaded and feared,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you lied and failed",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to remember Me or take this to heart?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Is it not because I have long been silent",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that you do not fear Me?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will expose your righteousness and your works,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will not profit you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When you cry out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let your companies of idols deliver you!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet the wind will carry off all of them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a breath will take them away.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But he who seeks refuge in Me will inherit the land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and possess My holy mountain.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Healing for the Repentant"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "And it will be said,",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Build it up, build it up, prepare the way,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "take every obstacle out of the way of My people.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For thus says the One who is high and lifted up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who inhabits eternity, whose name is Holy:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I dwell in a high and holy place,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and with the oppressed and humble in spirit,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to restore the spirit of the lowly",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and revive the heart of the contrite.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I will not accuse you forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will I always be angry;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for then the spirit of man would grow weak before Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with the breath of those I have made.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I was enraged by his sinful greed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so I struck him and hid My face in anger;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet he kept turning back",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the desires of his heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have seen his ways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but I will heal him;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will guide him and restore comfort",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to him and his mourners,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "bringing praise to their lips.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Peace, peace to those far and near,” says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“and I will heal them.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the wicked are like the storm-tossed sea,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for it cannot be still,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and its waves churn up mire and muck.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“There is no peace,” says my God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“for the wicked.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
